items.name: Kakao - Artist Style (LoRa/Lycoris)
items.description:
If you enjoyed this model, why don't you check out my other works? I put a lot of effort into correctly recreating artist styles and making the occasional character LoRA.üòä

This model was trained using the collab/guide by holostrawberry [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free - colabs | Stable Diffusion Other | Civitai

About the artist:

Twitter: kakao‚ñ°ÂçòË°åÊú¨5ÊúàÊú´Áô∫Â£≤ (@kakao_3percent) / Twitter

Pixiv: kakao - pixiv

Kakao creates hentai manga which means this model is very nsfw.

Weights & Prompts

The model is activated by the prompt:

kakao

Lycoris:

This should be your goto model for most checkpoints, allowing for more flexibility.

Use a weight of 1.0, adjust to taste. For reference check the XYZ plot in the examples.

LoRA:

Only use this with models based on Abyss Orange Mix.

Use a weight of 0.9-1.0. Go a bit lower (I used 0.7-0.8) for character loras. As usual I have included XYZ plots for reference.

It can be helpful to include "text" in the negative prompts as many of the training images were doujin covers but it is not absolutely necessary.

I was pleasently surprised when creating landscapes as they are a bit more surreal but a lot less generic than AOM3 by itself. You can finde 4 images of the same prompt with and without the LoRA above.

Please leave a review if you enjoyed this model or have problems with it. This helps me with improving future models and finetuning them in general. Give it a try and throw some images down below! üëá

Checkpoint Type: SDXL/Zero Limitations/Everything/Everywhere

Support me on Twitter: @YamerOfficial

Welcome to "Unstable Diffusers" now with a SDXL upgrade, this is a collection of checkpoints where limitations cease to exist and creativity knows no bounds and is the only thing remaining. This checkpoint defies restrictions and empowers you to generate anything your imagination desires; üñåÔ∏è

You may stumble upon the pinnacle of perfection with a specific prompt or encounter a delightful chaos of visuals. Embrace the adventure and discover for yourself what works best. Good luck in your artistic endeavors fellow creator!

This checkpoint was created with the intent to be unstable, with that I mean that it was created using a huge variety of models, the ustable diffusers models are both trained and merged, these are the models that will usually give you the best results in any type of style because of the huge quantity of styles if can reproduce.

  • No embedding needed

items.name: AlanahPearce Face
items.description:
NOTE this TI is old and not very good, but it has since served it's purpose as there are now some good quality models out there for Alanah. Check out the LoCon by malcomrey for a better model.

I trained a Textual Inversion model on one of my favorite youtubers turned game designer, Alanah Pearce, and after some tinkering I was able to get some decent gens out of it so it's time to share.

I seem to get best results by using the keyword as ((alanah_pearce:0.89)) at least when using fitCorderMixV2.1 as my checkpoint. (NOTE: ((alanah_pearce_face:0.89)) also works and provides slightly different results, try it out. Both are pretty touchy and like to either overburn, or look nothing like her. YMMV with other models. (GalaxyTimeMachineV3 also produced some decent results)

The negative embedding is optional, it may help with some models, and it may hinder you with others. Try with and without it, and try modifying the strength of the negative embed in contrast with the strength of the positive embedding until something comes together decently.

This was trained on a set of 32 images pulled from public sources (Reddit, Instagram, YouTube) using A1111's "Train" tab for embeddings. I unfortunately don't recall the specific settings used, but there's definitely still room for improvement on this one.

Erin Stout from Critical Miss. Trained on NAI. Tested at 0.8-1.0 strength.

items.name: Polina - Tiny Bunny
items.description:
LoRA which will allow you to create images with Polina from the game Tiny Bunny.

Weights:

I recommend using a weight of 0.67 for the best generation, but you can try experimenting with weights from 0.5 to 0.8.

The model can make color images, just add a black and white token to the negative prompt

Enjoy using it!

modelVersions.name: v1.1
modelVersions.description:
I used other settings during training, thereby correcting some problems.

Now Lora will not spoil the quality of generation.

items.name: Lulu Chu
items.description:
Lulu Chu is an American adult film actress, model, and social media influencer.

Trained on 1.5 base model but examples are on Analog Madness

Is surprisingly SFW, in most of it's renders, as none of the pictures used were adult in nature

Please let me know what you think of this model/suggestions/criticism and most importantly requests for the next model to make.

items.name: Neimi (Fire Emblem)
items.description:
Neimi from Fire Emblem Sacred Stones.

Tested at 0.6-0.9 weight. Trigger word is neimi fe.

Prompt for default look: neimi fe, short hair, gloves, elbow gloves, pants, hood, fingerless gloves, headband, asymmetrical clothes, asymmetrical gloves.

The FEH splash screen effects like to make their way into the gens, so maybe either neg prompt "simple background, black background" or prompt a background for the AI to work with.

Kind of limited data, the asymetrical elements like the glove and the shoulder armor are very hard to get on the right place.

Cheryl from Pokemon Diamond/Pearl. Trained on NAI. Tested at 0.8-1.0 strength.

A request from the form. Check out my Discord if you want to chat about video games (or yell at me about requests.)

This fan version still has some issues, (occasional outbreaks of too many eyes, cute but weird stub feet), and right now they're very... furry dustballs, I thought I'd release the V1 while I work on making it better.

They eat Star Candy. :D

Have fun!

items.name: Lissandra | League of Legends
items.description:
LoRA trained on Lissandra from League of Legends

Coven Lissandra will be next

Initially, it was planned as a 2-in-1, but the helmet bleed into the other one even with Loha, so they will be separate

models used

anime: YabaL_Mix V3(image 7,12,13), MeinaAlter,

2,5D: DarkSun, HELLmix, GhostMix(image 2,3,8,9,10,11), MeinaUnreal - V3(image 1,5,6)

realistic: Paragon V1.0(image 4)

tags: lissandra, 1girl, blue skin

optional tags: helmet, long dress, pauldrons, braid, white hair, helmet over eyes

negative embeddings: embedding:bad-hands-5, embedding:ng_deepnegative_v1_75t, embedding:bad-artist, embedding:EasyNegative

Recommended settings:

  • Make sure you are aware on the usage instructions of LORA

  • VAE: vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned (for realistic models & 2,5D), kl-f8-anime2, blessed2.vae (for anime models)

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras or DPM++ 2M Karras

  • Steps: 20 to 35

  • Clipskip: 2

  • Upscaler : img2img in comfyui using 4x-UltraSharp(for 2,5D & realistic), 4xAnimesharp(for anime)

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 9 (mostly 7)

  • LORA weight for txt2img: 0.5-1 (for the examples i mostly used 0.8)

  • Denoise strength for img2img: 0.4 to 0.7

for the pictures i used comfyui

I've been using this model to generate background images for my AI driven Text-based RPG game at www.forgesaga.com and enjoyed the results so much I had to share it with the community too.

painting of ..., late night, dusk, night, dark, starlit, fantasy, medieval, loading screen art, <lora:epiNoiseoffset_v2:0.2>, <lora:howlbgsv3:0.5>, <lora:artbytokiame:0.5>, <lora:add_detail:0.3>, ink outlines, wallpaper, vignette, matte painting by (Kazimir Malevich:1.1), simple lighting, dynamic shading, complementary colors, HDR, absurdres, cinematic, muted colors, limited color pallete, (masterpiece:1.2), (best quality:1.1)

NEGATIVE:
realistic, character, people, photograph, 3d render, blurry, grayscale, oversaturated, bad-hands-5, easynegative, photozoov15, structurezoov15, verybadimagenegative_v1.3, cropped, (watermark, logo, signature, text, signature:1.4)

Settings:
"cfg_scale": 7, "sampler_name": "Euler a", "steps": 40

To get the results above, I personally run my generations through a second img2img pass at 0.45 noise with the same settings and a canny controlnet of 0.3 to keep the general shapes intact.

I then do a final upscale to final resolution.

Enjoy!

items.name: Accent Wall - Stucco Veneziano
items.description:
Combining Italian-born stucco paint and advanced Japanese construction techniques, Stucco Plus Inc( https://stuccoplus.co.jp ). is developing the fascination of singular plaster finishes in the digital world. Our unique finishing technique is presented as the Lora model, allowing you to give shape to your imagination. This project, which is still growing, will continue to evolve alongside our technology.

Using SegmentAnything and Inpaint together, you can draw a lively perspective image of your home before and after the renovation. Seeing the remodelling image change in real time will help you realise your ideal space. When your creativity is inspired, please share your work with us. We look forward to seeing your ideas.

The new Lora model Veneziano is characterised by a mirror-like shine created by the exquisite lustre of the marble powder. It adapts to any space and creates a sophisticated interior with its mere presence. Achieve a luxurious and refined space in an instant with this model.

A strength of 0.7-0.8 is recommended.

LoRA trained on Coven Lissandra from League of Legends

requested by @Cinders

2,5D: DarkSun(image 1,2,3,4,7), HELLmix, GhostMix, MeinaUnreal - V3

negative embeddings: embedding:bad-hands-5, embedding:ng_deepnegative_v1_75t, embedding:bad-artist, embedding:EasyNegative

Recommended settings:

  • Make sure you are aware on the usage instructions of LORA

  • VAE: vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned (for realistic models & 2,5D), kl-f8-anime2, blessed2.vae (for anime models)

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras or DPM++ 2M Karras

  • Clipskip: 2

  • Upscaler : img2img in comfyui using 4x-UltraSharp(for 2,5D & realistic), 4xAnimesharp(for anime)

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 9 (mostly 7)

  • LORA weight for txt2img: 0.5-1 (for the examples i mostly used 0.8)

  • Denoise strength for img2img: 0.4 to 0.7

for full body shots i recommend using: ComfyUI Impact Pack

or the a1111 alternative GitHub - dustysys/ddetailer

English Explanation:

This is LoRA to suppress the worst quality of the picture.

It is recommended to apply at -0.3.

The content is simple, learning images made with "worst quality, male, blurry".

By applying negative values ‚Äã‚Äãto such low-quality images, it is possible to suppress them.

You no longer need to add nevative prompt like "worst quality, low quality", etc.

I made it aiming for something like flat2 or EasyNegative, but rather than improving the quality,it's like keep quality not to down.

Have you ever experienced the dropping quality suddenly when applying multiple LoRAs and tweaking these values?

In other words, over-using LoRAs made the worst quality.

suppressing it is my primary purpose.

The image should have five qualities: worst, low, normal, high, and best,

but if you suppress only worst,It should be used widely from the remaining low to best, so it has a soft and slightly bokeh feel rather than a over-sharpness.

It seems to have a softer finish.

I used that ChillOutMix_Ni plus 30% BRAv5 merged model, and it is especially effective for these two.

for positive prompts, "realistic,photo" is good enough. you don't have to limit to best quality.
